      },
      "date": "2013-02-06 07:34:24.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\n(1 inline comment)\n\nPer discussion in Skype, the existing ROOT FID should be kept (IGIF or normal FID).  I believe that LFSCK will already do the work to add this into the LMA and OI.  Only FID_SEQ_LOCAL should be replaced by FID_SEQ_ROOT (if it is in use anywhere at all).  Newly-formatted filesystems with no ROOT should use FID_SEQ_ROOT.\n\nI think this patch will likely also need to be rebased on the LFSCK patches, which are touching the same code.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "a4619e617e70da7cef9ce37d289405fb1a25791d",
